# 📚 Key Concepts

| Concept | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Spring Boot | Framework for creating stand-alone Java applications |
| REST API | Communication between applications using HTTP |
| RestTemplate | Spring class used to consume REST APIs |
| @RestController | Marks the class as a REST Controller |
| @GetMapping | Maps HTTP GET requests to methods |
| @Autowired | Automatically injects dependencies |
| @Bean | Registers RestTemplate as a Spring Bean |
| Synchronous Call | Client waits until the server responds |

---

# ⚡ Synchronous Call Characteristics

- Client waits for the server response.
- Blocking communication.
- Simple to implement.
- Suitable for small applications.
- Higher response time if the server is slow.

